By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – Nigeria Centre for Disease Control has said that COVID-19 cases shrinked on Sunday as only 138 cases were recorded from 14 states in Nigeria. While 20 states reported cases with 250 infections on Saturday, 14 states reported cases with 138 cases on Sunday. According to the report released by NCDC via its twitter handle, the fresh cases bring total confirmed cases to 53,865 out of which 41,513 have been  discharged. The death toll has also risen to 1,013, the health agency maintained. The infections report reads: Plateau-55 Lagos-15 Ebonyi-11 Oyo-11 Abia-8 Anambra-7 FCT-7 Rivers-7 Kaduna-6 Ondo-5 Kwara-3 Bauchi-1 Benue-1 Edo-1 See the  state by state breakdown  below: ByChibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The Nigeria's COVID-19 death toll on Sunday hit 1,002 as the Centre for Disease Control reported 322 new confirmed cases. The report released by the Nigeria Centre for Disease control via its twitter handle has it that the new cases were recorded from 18… August 24, 2020 In "Top Stories" By Abujah Racheal ABUJA - The number of COVID-19 cases in Nigeria has reached 37, 225, the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports. According to the latest data released by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control, (NCDC) on its official twitter handle on Monday, 562 new cases were reported. The… July 21, 2020 In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuk Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The reported cases of COVID-19 infections Thursday shrunk to 373 compared to the 473 cases recorded on Wednesday, the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control report has shown. However, there was a reported increase in death toll from 956 the previous day (Wednesday) to… August 14, 2020 In "Top Stories"